text:
Ordered the $7 sambal petal with minced meat rice. (as shown in the display photos)
However, there was no egg when the food was served.. The staff said no eggs after 5pm. This was cheating!
It was not mentioned when I placed the orders and it was not stated in the display as well. It stated "add egg for $1 after 5pm" My first and last time eating here.
The tom yum seafood soup is spicy but very fragrant.
Had the seafood yam ring, it was delicious and had a nice mix of textures.
The cereal prawns were crunchy and had a great sweet and savoury balance
The sweet and sour pork was perfectly balanced, crispy coating.
